1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:15,000
 Well, it's so good to see you. Happy 2026. Happy New Year. Sun and phylog. Sun and ginkgong. You know, like all those things. I'm going to stop. I need to save some for Chinese New Year.

2
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:27,000
 But yeah, it's great to see you. And I know at the beginning of the year, we, a lot, for a lot of us, we hold actually quite different emotions and feelings as we step into the new year.

3
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:40,000
 Now, some of us were excited. Maybe you have a new job and you're just excited where that's going to take you or you know you're going to be graduating or you have a big special date that's coming up that you're going to be celebrating.

4
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:47,000
 Or maybe it's time with your family or a vacation or something like that. And you're like, man, I'm excited about 2026. And that's awesome.

5
00:00:47,000 --> 00:01:03,000
 Praise God for that, if that is your outlook for 2026. Then there's a lot of us were like, well, 2026, kind of like 2025, a little bit same old, same old, you know, moving, moving.

6
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:21,000
 It's last year. Same old, same old. Exactly. And you're like, you know, you don't have any special particular feelings about 2026. You're just moving forward.

7
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:33,000
 But I know there's also some of us who are actually dreading 2026, you know, for different reasons. And actually that weighs quite heavily on you.

8
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:42,000
 And so I don't know which group you're part of, you know, what your feelings are that you're holding today. But I want to tell you what I do know.

9
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:54,000
 I know that God loves every single one of you. I know that God has given us each other the journey with each other through this year.

10
00:01:54,000 --> 00:02:04,000
 I know that God is mighty and powerful and able to do immeasurably more than all we can ask for or imagine.

11
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:13,000
 I know that His grace is sufficient for us and that God's power is demonstrated in our weakness.

12
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:23,000
 And I know that God is faithful and that He is with us. Can I hear an amen? Amen.

13
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:36,000
 But there is a question, you know, how are we personally stepping into 2026, not 2025? Otherwise you're doing something quite amazing.

14
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:49,000
 It'd be a miracle, right? But how are we stepping into 2026? Are we stepping in close to Jesus or are we actually quite disconnected from God?

15
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:56,000
 So what I want to explore with you today through this message is this question.

16
00:02:56,000 --> 00:03:09,000
 You know, how can I draw close to God, experience His presence, power and love in my life this year like I have never experienced it before?

17
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:15,000
 You know, how do I do that? How do I make more room for more of God in my life?

18
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:25,000
 That's what I want to unpack with you. So this year, as Pastor Chapman already announced, we are doing a corporate fast.

19
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:33,000
 So we fast together as a church. It's a divine tradition. I've been doing this for eight years now, so you know how long I've been at the Vine.

20
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:39,000
 And it's been an incredible blessing to me to have a 21-day fast, the start of the year.

21
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:46,000
 It's a way of aligning ourselves with God, of opening our lives for more of God in our lives.

22
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:54,000
 And for making room for God to powerfully work wherever we need Him to work and to ask Him and invite Him into that.

23
00:03:54,000 --> 00:04:01,000
 And so I'm excited. One of the great blessings of this fast is that we get to do it together.

24
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:05,000
 You're not doing it by yourself. There's actually power in seeking God together.

25
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:12,000
 It's so encouraging to know you're not the only one who's doing this. And so I'm excited about that as well.

26
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:23,000
 Now, the fast is starting tomorrow, January 5th, and it's going to last until January 25th.

27
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:29,000
 So you can have today to kind of sort out how you want to be part of it, decide whether or not you want to be part of it.

28
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:35,000
 Of course, my encouragement is be part of it. That's my challenge to you.

29
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:42,000
 And we're going to, as Pastor Chapman said, we're going to be sending out devotionals written by us, by our community,

30
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:46,000
 that can help us draw close to God through His Word, through prayers.

31
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:54,000
 And I want to just give a shout out to my team. So I told them last year, I don't have the energy to drive any of this.

32
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:59,000
 And they did it. So they have organized it. They have put it together.

33
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:06,000
 So a big shout out to Ivan, June, Talitha, and Chapman.

34
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:12,000
 [applause]

35
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:16,000
 Now I want to share with you also a verse that encourages us to draw near to God.

36
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:24,000
 It's from James 4, verse 8. It says, "Come near to God, and He will come near to you."

37
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:35,000
 That is a promise. So as we seek Him, God meets us. He will meet us. He will meet you.

38
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:41,000
 Now, if you're like me, I grew up in an environment where people didn't talk much about fasting.

39
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:47,000
 It was like this thing, every once in a while, if you read your Bible, you came across it, and then you moved on.

40
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:53,000
 I didn't really know what it was. I didn't really know what to do. And I didn't really see any spiritual significance in it.

41
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:58,000
 And so I thought today, it would be good to actually talk about what is fasting, why do we fast.

42
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:03,000
 And so that's what I want to spend time on with you here.

43
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:07,000
 Now, what is fasting, and why do we do it?

44
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:15,000
 Well, Jesus, it's interesting, He actually assumes that we are fasting.

45
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:23,000
 So if you go to Matthew 6, verse 16, it says this, "When you fast."

46
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:27,000
 So it's not like if you feel like fasting, or perhaps you will fast, or some of you might be fasting.

47
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:32,000
 It's like, when you fast. He's assuming that His disciples are fasting.

48
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:38,000
 "Do not look somber, as hypocrites do, for they disfigure their faces to show others they are fasting.

49
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:42,000
 Truly I tell you, they have received their full and reward."

50
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:49,000
 Now, Jesus is talking about not acting hypocritically, and making sure that other people know that you're fasting,

51
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:53,000
 and trying to look good in front of them, instead of caring about your relationship with God.

52
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:57,000
 So fasting is about a relationship with God.

53
00:06:57,000 --> 00:07:03,000
 But then I want to also take you to what I think is a key teaching on fasting in the New Testament.

54
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:08,000
 And that's in Matthew, chapter 9, verse 14 and 15, it says this,

55
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:17,000
 "Then John's disciples came and asked him, 'How is it that we and the Pharisees fast often, but your disciples do not fast?'

56
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:23,000
 Jesus answered, 'How can the guest of the bridegroom mourn while he is with them?

57
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:30,000
 For the time will come when the bridegroom will be taken from them, and they will fast.'"

58
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:33,000
 Now, what's going on here?

59
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:40,000
 Well, John's disciples, or from John the Baptist's disciples, are asking Jesus, "Why are your disciples not fasting?"

60
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:46,000
 And they're wondering about that, because during that time, part of the normal spiritual practice,

61
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:55,000
 especially for those who are serious about their faith, was to fast twice, twice a week.

62
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:59,000
 And they're like, "Hey, you guys are feasting, but you're not fasting.

63
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:03,000
 Are you not serious about God? What's going on here?"

64
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:07,000
 And I love Jesus and how he responds, as he does so many times.

65
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:08,000
 He responds with a question.

66
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:14,000
 He actually says, "How can the guest of the bridegroom mourn while he is with them?"

67
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:18,000
 Now, what you have to know is, during that time, if there was a wedding celebration,

68
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:22,000
 it lasted usually for seven days, so a big party.

69
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:28,000
 And if you were part of that wedding celebration, you were not allowed to fast,

70
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:33,000
 because it was a joyous season, and it was not a time for mourning.

71
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:40,000
 And so Jesus is saying, "I am the bridegroom. I am right now. I have come. I'm here.

72
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:44,000
 And this is a joyous occasion that I have come."

73
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:50,000
 And so that's why the disciples, who in this metaphor are the guests, they're not fasting.

74
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:56,000
 And Jesus is drawing on the prophet Isaiah in chapter 25,

75
00:08:56,000 --> 00:09:01,000
 where he talks about a time when there will be a messianic banquet, a wedding banquet,

76
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:06,000
 when the kingdom of God is fully established.

77
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:12,000
 And we get to have table fellowship with God, and that is a joyous occasion.

78
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:19,000
 And so what Jesus is saying, actually the reason why religious people in that time are fasting

79
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:22,000
 is because they want God to act.

80
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:27,000
 They want God to move in their lives, in their nation's lives.

81
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:33,000
 And he's saying, "Well, I am acting, and I'm here, because Jesus is God with us.

82
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:39,000
 Something incredible is happening, and so it's time to feast and not time to fast."

83
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:43,000
 But then he continues.

84
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:50,000
 He says, "The time will come when the bridegroom will be taken from men, and they will fast."

85
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:53,000
 So he's talking about our time period.

86
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:59,000
 Jesus, he died, he rose, he ascended to heaven.

87
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:04,000
 And he says, "In this time in between when the kingdom of God is inaugurated,

88
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:07,000
 when the kingdom of God has broken into this world,

89
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:11,000
 until the time when the kingdom comes in all its fullness, when Jesus comes again,

90
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:15,000
 his people will fast. They will seek him.

91
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:18,000
 They will express their longing, their need, their hunger for God,

92
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:21,000
 for more of God in their lives, for more of God in their city,

93
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:27,000
 for more of God in their community, for more of God in their brokenness, in their sin."

94
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:30,000
 So this is what fasting is about.

95
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:37,000
 It's a cry of a heart. It's actually the cry of the Lord's prayer.

96
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:41,000
 The second and the third petition, "Your kingdom come.

97
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:49,000
 Your will be done on earth as it is in heaven."

98
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:54,000
 Lord, we need you to break into our current situation.

99
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:58,000
 We need your reign. We need your salvation.

100
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:02,000
 We need your power to come bear on our current situation.

101
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:05,000
 That's what fasting is about.

102
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:09,000
 It's this longing. It's a cry of a heart.

103
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:14,000
 Fasting is always a sacred, grievous moment.

104
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:17,000
 Now, what is a sacred, grievous moment?

105
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:24,000
 There is always something that weighs on our heart because something is broken.

106
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:28,000
 Something is not right. Something is not the way it ought to be.

107
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:31,000
 That's a sacred, grievous moment and we feel the weight of it.

108
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:37,000
 And because of that, we come before God in prayer and in fasting.

109
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:45,000
 We say, "Lord, will you break into the sacred, grievous moment of myself, of the city,

110
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:52,000
 and will you act, 'Your kingdom come, your will be done on earth as it is in heaven'?"

111
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:56,000
 You know, that's that cry of our fasting.

112
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:59,000
 So here's a definition for you.

113
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:05,000
 "Christian fasting and prayer is the passionate pursuit of the not yet of the kingdom,

114
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:12,000
 a longing for the establishment of God's reign in our present circumstances."

115
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:18,000
 And so our fasting is an expression of our sacred, grievous moments

116
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:26,000
 where we need God to act and move and meet us and meet our community.

117
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:31,000
 It's where things are not the way they ought to be.

118
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:36,000
 Where we want God's power to come in and restore things and make them whole

119
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:43,000
 and bring us peace and shalom into our relationships that are broken with God,

120
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:46,000
 our relationships that are broken with each other,

121
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:49,000
 our relationships that even are broken with ourselves,

122
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:54,000
 and our relationships that are broken with creation.

123
00:12:54,000 --> 00:13:00,000
 And we just long and we cry out to God for God to act and meet us.

124
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:04,000
 And so the kingdom of God with Jesus coming was inaugurated, or it began.

125
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:11,000
 It means God's power, His reign has broken in, sin, death has been defeated,

126
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:16,000
 captives are set free, people are healed.

127
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:20,000
 So with that we talk about the kingdom is all ready.

128
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:24,000
 But we also say the kingdom is not fully yet,

129
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:29,000
 because there still is brokenness, there still is pain.

130
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:33,000
 And so we wait for the fullness of the kingdom.

131
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:36,000
 Now there are two things that Christians a lot of times do.

132
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:38,000
 I should say that we do.

133
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:40,000
 Two things we a lot of times do.

134
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:45,000
 The first one is we live in the not yet,

135
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:48,000
 and we over-emphasize the not yet of the kingdom.

136
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:51,000
 We pretend as if God doesn't do anything right now,

137
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:56,000
 and only when we go to heaven or when God brings heaven down to this earth,

138
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:59,000
 that's when He will act.

139
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:02,000
 And that's actually quite hopeless.

140
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:07,000
 And it's not taking serious that Jesus has come and has set captives free

141
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:12,000
 and is setting captives free, that the kingdom of God is advancing now and here.

142
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:17,000
 So that's a lot of times we over-emphasize the not yet.

143
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:19,000
 But then there's a flip side.

144
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:23,000
 Sometimes there's groups of us that over-emphasize already,

145
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:27,000
 like as if there's all the fullness of the kingdom, there is no problems.

146
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:29,000
 You can't even share your problem,

147
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:32,000
 because then that means you don't have faith.

148
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:35,000
 And that's not truthful either, because we know there is still brokenness.

149
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:38,000
 There are still things where we need God to move, to act,

150
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:42,000
 with His power, by His grace, by His Holy Spirit.

151
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:46,000
 And so we're meant to live in that tension of the already, but not yet,

152
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:50,000
 but with hope, with faith, that God is at work,

153
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:53,000
 that He has not abandoned this world, He has not abandoned you,

154
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:56,000
 and He is advancing the kingdom and moving it forward.

155
00:14:56,000 --> 00:15:02,000
 And so with that faith, we can come before God with our fasting and with our prayers.

156
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:09,000
 So fasting is a prophetic declaration of hope

157
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:14,000
 that whatever might be going on, whatever the circumstances are,

158
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:19,000
 whatever seems like a lost cause, it is not the final word.

159
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:22,000
 God is not finished with us yet.

160
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:25,000
 God is not finished with you yet.

161
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:30,000
 God is not finished with this city yet.

162
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:34,000
 He is present and He is at work.

163
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:38,000
 And so when we fast, it is a prophetic act of faith

164
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:43,000
 that God is at work, that the final word has not been spoken,

165
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:45,000
 that things are not over yet,

166
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:52,000
 because God has a power to do immeasurably more than we can ask or imagine.

167
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:54,000
 Amen, that's right.

168
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:56,000
 Yes.

169
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:59,000
 So I want to ask you this.

170
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:12,000
 As you step into 2026, where do you need guidance, provision, breakthrough, wisdom?

171
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:20,000
 What's your sacred, grievous moment?

172
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:26,000
 What are you going to fast about and especially focus on during this fasting time?

173
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:29,000
 Is it something in our city?

174
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:33,000
 Is it something in your own life?

175
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:40,000
 Where do you need God to break into your not yet moment?

176
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:45,000
 So think about that.

177
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:53,000
 He's inviting us to draw near to Him through fasting and through prayer,

178
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:57,000
 because God loves meeting us, He loves working in our lives.

179
00:16:57,000 --> 00:17:00,000
 And there's something when we come in the surrendered way,

180
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:02,000
 when we make space for God,

181
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:07,000
 that God loves coming and working in us and meeting us.

182
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:12,000
 Now I do have to say one thing in addition to that.

183
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:15,000
 Sometimes fasting is presented like a vending machine, right?

184
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:19,000
 I fast, I put, here's a bada tong, you don't put money in here anymore.

185
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:23,000
 Use your bada tong, your octopus card,

186
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:27,000
 and you push the machine, out comes the coke,

187
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:31,000
 or whatever it is that you drink, healthy drinks, I assume you all drink water, right?

188
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:37,000
 And that's a lot of times how we view fasting.

189
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:42,000
 I can twist God's arm to give me what I want, but that's not it.

190
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:46,000
 So actually fasting is surrendering and saying, "Lord, I need you."

191
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:48,000
 And it's trusting that He will meet us,

192
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:51,000
 but He will meet us how He wants to meet us.

193
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:53,000
 That can be His grace is sufficient for us,

194
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:56,000
 that can be He removes whatever's going on and transforms it and changes it.

195
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:58,000
 God can meet us how He wants to,

196
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:02,000
 but we just come surrendered and we believe that God meets us

197
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:05,000
 and that because we come to Him,

198
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:08,000
 whatever's going on will be different because He meets us.

199
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:12,000
 Now, some of you might be wondering,

200
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:15,000
 "Well, okay, so you talk about fasting and drawing close to God,

201
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:20,000
 and what is actually fasting like? What do you actually do?"

202
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:23,000
 Now, biblically, fasting always involves not eating food

203
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:27,000
 or restraining yourself from food in some way or form.

204
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:30,000
 And then drinking water and seeking, expressing with that hunger,

205
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:32,000
 that "Lord, I need you."

206
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:36,000
 There's the Daniel fast, where Daniel seeks God for 21 days,

207
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:40,000
 and he doesn't eat any choice foods, doesn't drink any wine,

208
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:45,000
 and he's longing for God to meet him and to provide for him.

209
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:47,000
 So there's that.

210
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:49,000
 And so if you choose to fast from food,

211
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:54,000
 we recommend that you either skip a meal or that you do a Daniel fast.

212
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:57,000
 If you fully want to do a hardcore fast,

213
00:18:57,000 --> 00:19:00,000
 please do talk to your medical professional,

214
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:05,000
 because that is quite serious and it will not be good for everyone.

215
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:07,000
 But there's another way of fasting,

216
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:14,000
 and that's setting aside something that crowds out our time with God.

217
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:17,000
 And I think for me, actually, it's probably harder

218
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:22,000
 to fast from social media than it is to fast from food.

219
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:24,000
 Right?

220
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:27,000
 And so some of us choose to maybe fast from Instagram.

221
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:29,000
 Maybe that's how you start your day.

222
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:33,000
 You're scrolling, you wake up, and the first thing is you're doing that.

223
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:37,000
 You're doing that, or you're looking at YouTube or Netflix or whatever.

224
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:39,000
 And so you can set that aside.

225
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:42,000
 You can say, "Lord, I need you more than I need those things.

226
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:44,000
 I hunger for you more than I need those things,

227
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:47,000
 and I want to make room for you."

228
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:49,000
 But here's something really important.

229
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:53,000
 You know, fasting is not just abstaining from something.

230
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:55,000
 Sometimes when I hear people talk about fasting,

231
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:59,000
 especially if it's like the Lent period,

232
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:01,000
 it's like, "Oh, I'm not going to eat chocolate."

233
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:03,000
 And it's like, "Great, you're not eating chocolate,

234
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:07,000
 but how does that bring you closer to God?"

235
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:09,000
 So fasting isn't just giving up something.

236
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:11,000
 It's making room for someone.

237
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:14,000
 It's making room for God.

238
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:17,000
 And so that means we actually need to create this time

239
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:20,000
 where we pray and seek God through prayer,

240
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:24,000
 where we seek God through his word.

241
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:27,000
 And the way you can do that is, like, if you're skipping a meal,

242
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:33,000
 you can seek God during that time where you usually would eat that meal.

243
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:38,000
 If you're not watching social media or scrolling,

244
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:44,000
 you can use some of that time to seek God in prayer and through his word.

245
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:46,000
 Now, I want to talk a little bit.

246
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:52,000
 I did sense for us this year that God does want us to focus more on his word,

247
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:54,000
 to seek him more through his word.

248
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:56,000
 So I want to talk a little bit about that.

249
00:20:56,000 --> 00:21:00,000
 And that also applies to our fasting, how we fill that time.

250
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:03,000
 We don't just abstain, but we fill that time with God.

251
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:05,000
 So I want to speak into that a little bit.

252
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:09,000
 Now, the Apostle Paul, he encourages his protege,

253
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:12,000
 one of his coworkers, Timothy,

254
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:18,000
 and one way he encourages him is by saying to keep God's word central in his life,

255
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:21,000
 to not give up on that.

256
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:26,000
 Second Timothy 3, 14 through 17 says this,

257
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:31,000
 "But as for you, continue in what you have learned and have firmly believed,

258
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:36,000
 knowing from whom you learned it and how from childhood you have been acquainted

259
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:40,000
 with the sacred writings, which are able to make you wise for salvation

260
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:43,000
 through faith in Christ Jesus.

261
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:47,000
 All scriptures breathed out by God and profitable for teaching,

262
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:51,000
 for reproof, for correction, and for training in righteousness,

263
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:58,000
 that the man of God may be competent, equipped for every good work."

264
00:21:58,000 --> 00:22:04,000
 So why does Paul encourage Timothy to keep God's word central?

265
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:06,000
 I want to give two reasons for that.

266
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:09,000
 There's more in here, but I want to give two.

267
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:14,000
 The first one is the nature of God's word.

268
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:18,000
 If you look at verse 16, it talks about breathed out by God.

269
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:23,000
 That's how it describes that all scripture is breathed out by God.

270
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:27,000
 That is the Greek word theopneustos,

271
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:33,000
 and it can also be translated as God breathed or inspired by God.

272
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:36,000
 It's the only time this word is used in the Bible.

273
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:41,000
 What this means and what this is referencing is Genesis 2, 7,

274
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:46,000
 where God breathed life into Adam.

275
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:51,000
 He's saying this word, "I have breathed my life,"

276
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:53,000
 whatever that is, you know it, you can fill it in.

277
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:57,000
 Whatever it is, "I've breathed my life into this word."

278
00:22:57,000 --> 00:23:00,000
 This is not just like reading something else.

279
00:23:00,000 --> 00:23:04,000
 This is a word that is alive and living.

280
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:08,000
 God speaks to us when we seek him through his word.

281
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:10,000
 He speaks to us.

282
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:11,000
 He makes himself known.

283
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:15,000
 He reveals himself by his word and by his spirit.

284
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:20,000
 Paul is encouraging Timothy to keep God's word central

285
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:25,000
 because the word is God breathed.

286
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:27,000
 It's the same for us.

287
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:32,000
 We need to get into God's word because the very life of God,

288
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:35,000
 the breath of God is in this word, and he makes himself known to you.

289
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:37,000
 He speaks to you through his word.

290
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:43,000
 Now, the second thing is Paul talks about the purpose of God's word,

291
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:47,000
 and that's a reason for why keeping God's word central in our lives.

292
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:52,000
 He gives five reasons, and I'm going to go through them very quickly.

293
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:56,000
 The first one, the first purpose of God's word is that it makes us,

294
00:23:56,000 --> 00:23:58,000
 in verse 15, wise.

295
00:23:58,000 --> 00:24:01,000
 It makes you wise for salvation.

296
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:06,000
 It means that God reveals himself to you personally,

297
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:10,000
 and you can come to know him, and you can come to a saving faith

298
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:13,000
 through the word of God.

299
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:15,000
 Now, I've seen this.

300
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:19,000
 When I spend time with people that are exploring the Christian faith

301
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:23,000
 and are reading God's word, and God comes alive,

302
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:27,000
 and they get to see God there being made,

303
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:34,000
 it makes you wise for salvation because God reveals himself to us.

304
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:36,000
 That's the first thing.

305
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:40,000
 But in verse 16, there are four more things that are listed there, basically.

306
00:24:40,000 --> 00:24:46,000
 So all scriptures breathe out by God and profit for teaching, reproof, correction,

307
00:24:46,000 --> 00:24:48,000
 and for training in righteousness.

308
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:52,000
 So I want to touch on those four things briefly.

309
00:24:52,000 --> 00:24:54,000
 The first one is teaching.

310
00:24:54,000 --> 00:24:58,000
 So God, through his word, by his spirit, he teaches about who he is,

311
00:24:58,000 --> 00:25:01,000
 who we are, what it means to know him, to follow him,

312
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:04,000
 how we should think about the world.

313
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:08,000
 So there's like a positive building up.

314
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:10,000
 And so God does that through his word.

315
00:25:10,000 --> 00:25:12,000
 We get to know God through his word.

316
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:15,000
 Then he reproofs us.

317
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:21,000
 So that means if we line up our thinking about God, ourselves, this world,

318
00:25:21,000 --> 00:25:24,000
 with God's word, what it says about ourselves, about him,

319
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:26,000
 about ourselves, and about this world,

320
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:29,000
 there is a lot of times something that's different.

321
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:31,000
 And so God's word reproves us.

322
00:25:31,000 --> 00:25:36,000
 It shows us our error, where we're off, where we're missing the mark.

323
00:25:36,000 --> 00:25:40,000
 But it doesn't only just tell you you're wrong.

324
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:42,000
 It also corrects us.

325
00:25:42,000 --> 00:25:48,000
 So that's the flip side of reproofing, where it gets us back on the right path,

326
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:51,000
 where it shows us how should we think about those things.

327
00:25:51,000 --> 00:25:57,000
 And then finally, it talks about that God's word trains us in righteousness

328
00:25:57,000 --> 00:26:01,000
 where it rears us in righteousness, like rearing a child.

329
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:09,000
 So that means it makes us learn and have more the character of Jesus,

330
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:15,000
 that we become more like God if we make room for God to speak into our lives.

331
00:26:15,000 --> 00:26:19,000
 And that's one thing that Paul is assuming here.

332
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:23,000
 There's an assumption of a posture that we bring to God's word.

333
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:29,000
 And that assumption is that we are surrendered to scripture and not above it.

334
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:34,000
 That it's not like what I feel like is what I believe and what I do.

335
00:26:34,000 --> 00:26:37,000
 And a lot of times we do that, we treat God's word as a buffet.

336
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:40,000
 We take the parts that I like, "Oh, this is an inspiring little clip,

337
00:26:40,000 --> 00:26:44,000
 and I like this verse, and I'll take this and put it on a mug,"

338
00:26:44,000 --> 00:26:46,000
 or something like that.

339
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:51,000
 But then ignoring a lot of other things that God's word says.

340
00:26:51,000 --> 00:26:57,000
 If we come with that sort of posture, if we're not surrendered to scripture,

341
00:26:57,000 --> 00:27:04,000
 we're not giving God's word and the spirit space to shape and mold us.

342
00:27:04,000 --> 00:27:12,000
 It's like getting feedback and not receiving it, and not being transformed.

343
00:27:12,000 --> 00:27:16,000
 Now, when I moved from Hong Kong--

344
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:19,000
 I've lived here before and then moved away, and now I came back.

345
00:27:19,000 --> 00:27:29,000
 So I moved to the US in 2013 to take over the church from a church planter

346
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:32,000
 who wanted to go and plant another church.

347
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:35,000
 Now, in this church they had a culture of feedback,

348
00:27:35,000 --> 00:27:38,000
 and I got feedback on everything.

349
00:27:38,000 --> 00:27:41,000
 I have to say, this was not easy for me.

350
00:27:41,000 --> 00:27:47,000
 I don't know if it's German nature or if it's just human pride.

351
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:49,000
 Man, it was hard for me to receive feedback.

352
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:53,000
 But I got feedback on everything, on every single sermon I got feedback on,

353
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:58,000
 every single event that I led, my leadership, everything.

354
00:27:58,000 --> 00:28:01,000
 And not just by a few people, by leadership,

355
00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:04,000
 but by a cross-section from the church.

356
00:28:04,000 --> 00:28:07,000
 So the university students were giving me feedback,

357
00:28:07,000 --> 00:28:09,000
 the young adults were giving me feedback,

358
00:28:09,000 --> 00:28:12,000
 the families were giving me feedback.

359
00:28:12,000 --> 00:28:16,000
 I got feedback for the rest of my life.

360
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:18,000
 But I had a choice, right?

361
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:25,000
 Do I submit to it, and am I open for people to input in my life or not?

362
00:28:25,000 --> 00:28:29,000
 And I chose to submit to it, and it was not always easy.

363
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:33,000
 It was not always easy because people don't always give perfect feedback, right?

364
00:28:33,000 --> 00:28:36,000
 So I had to learn how to chew the meat and spit out the bones,

365
00:28:36,000 --> 00:28:39,000
 like take what's good and grow from there,

366
00:28:39,000 --> 00:28:42,000
 and then let go of the things that are not good.

367
00:28:42,000 --> 00:28:45,000
 Now, in a similar but also a little bit different way,

368
00:28:45,000 --> 00:28:48,000
 God's Word is perfect, and He loves you perfectly.

369
00:28:48,000 --> 00:28:54,000
 For surrender to Scripture, we let God speak into our lives.

370
00:28:54,000 --> 00:28:59,000
 And because of it, it allows God through His Word and His Spirit

371
00:28:59,000 --> 00:29:05,000
 to shape and mold us and for us to flourish as individuals, as families,

372
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:09,000
 when we allow Him to do that work in our lives.

373
00:29:09,000 --> 00:29:11,000
 But it's a choice.

374
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:13,000
 And so during this fasting season, as we're seeking God,

375
00:29:13,000 --> 00:29:16,000
 as we're making space for God, one question is,

376
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:21,000
 are you surrender to Scripture, or are you above it?

377
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:25,000
 With what posture do you come before God?

378
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:31,000
 And if you're above it, you miss out on the work of God in your life.

379
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:35,000
 You know, that He wants to do it through His Word and His Spirit.

380
00:29:35,000 --> 00:29:43,000
 And that work is also further described in verse 17.

381
00:29:43,000 --> 00:29:52,000
 And it says that--here we go.

382
00:29:52,000 --> 00:29:58,000
 It makes you competent and equips you for every good work.

383
00:29:58,000 --> 00:30:01,000
 You know, when we allow God's Word to shape us,

384
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:07,000
 it makes you competent and equipped for every good work.

385
00:30:07,000 --> 00:30:12,000
 It allows you to become a blessing to other people.

386
00:30:12,000 --> 00:30:14,000
 Isn't that amazing?

387
00:30:14,000 --> 00:30:17,000
 I think that's amazing that God does work in our lives,

388
00:30:17,000 --> 00:30:21,000
 and it benefits ourselves because what God does is always good.

389
00:30:21,000 --> 00:30:22,000
 But it's not just for ourselves.

390
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:25,000
 It's actually to be a blessing to other people around us.

391
00:30:25,000 --> 00:30:27,000
 And so as we open ourselves up during fasting,

392
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:29,000
 it's not just about ourselves.

393
00:30:29,000 --> 00:30:32,000
 Even though we do bring our own needs to Him,

394
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:35,000
 but God also wants to do work in us as a community

395
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:45,000
 so that we can be a blessing to those around us.

396
00:30:45,000 --> 00:30:49,000
 Now, what might it look like to actually be surrendered to Scripture?

397
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:51,000
 So how do you actually do that, like when you read the Bible?

398
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:56,000
 It's nice to talk about it, but what does that look like?

399
00:30:56,000 --> 00:30:57,000
 How do you do that?

400
00:30:57,000 --> 00:31:00,000
 So there's one practice for me that I found helpful,

401
00:31:00,000 --> 00:31:05,000
 and I call it like paying attention to the highs and lows

402
00:31:05,000 --> 00:31:07,000
 as I prayerfully read Scripture.

403
00:31:07,000 --> 00:31:09,000
 Now, what are the highs and what are the lows?

404
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:13,000
 Well, the highs are words and verses that stick out to me

405
00:31:13,000 --> 00:31:16,000
 and that resonate deeply in my heart.

406
00:31:16,000 --> 00:31:19,000
 Like, they just pop out to you while you're reading it.

407
00:31:19,000 --> 00:31:21,000
 You're like, "Wow, there's something here."

408
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:25,000
 And for me, in this passage, the part that stuck out to me

409
00:31:25,000 --> 00:31:28,000
 was that we are made competent and equipped for every good work.

410
00:31:28,000 --> 00:31:32,000
 I was like, "Wow, that's amazing. That is so beautiful."

411
00:31:32,000 --> 00:31:35,000
 That part of God's shaping, forming work is not just for ourselves,

412
00:31:35,000 --> 00:31:38,000
 but it's for the sake of the world.

413
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:40,000
 So that's what stood out to me.

414
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:43,000
 But then there are also the lows, and lows doesn't mean it's bad,

415
00:31:43,000 --> 00:31:45,000
 but it's the part that challenges us.

416
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:48,000
 It's the verses that maybe unsettle you and you're not sitting right.

417
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:51,000
 And so maybe some of you, as I've been talking about it,

418
00:31:51,000 --> 00:31:55,000
 it's like reproof, correcting, feedback, what?

419
00:31:55,000 --> 00:31:57,000
 I don't want none of that.

420
00:31:57,000 --> 00:32:00,000
 That would be God's word.

421
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:03,000
 That would be a low where God is challenging you,

422
00:32:03,000 --> 00:32:07,000
 and that is an unsettling word to us.

423
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:11,000
 But it's always an area where the Spirit of God wants to do a work in our lives,

424
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:16,000
 and the highs and the lows, where He's doing something.

425
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:18,000
 And so we can pay attention to that

426
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:22,000
 and invite God into our lives there and surrender to Him.

427
00:32:22,000 --> 00:32:30,000
 Because being surrendered to Scripture ultimately means being surrendered to God.

428
00:32:30,000 --> 00:32:34,000
 Now, at the beginning we asked the question,

429
00:32:34,000 --> 00:32:39,000
 "How can I draw close to God and experience His presence, His power,

430
00:32:39,000 --> 00:32:45,000
 His love in my life in a greater measure?"

431
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:47,000
 And as we've gone through the sermon, we looked at,

432
00:32:47,000 --> 00:32:51,000
 "Well, one way that God gives us is to bring through fasting

433
00:32:51,000 --> 00:32:55,000
 our sacred, grievous moments before Him."

434
00:32:55,000 --> 00:33:00,000
 And we say, "Lord, I need You for 2026.

435
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:05,000
 I need You to powerfully work in this area of my life.

436
00:33:05,000 --> 00:33:10,000
 I need You to break in, because I'm experiencing right now the not yet,

437
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:14,000
 the brokenness, the hurt, the pain.

438
00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:16,000
 And I need You, Lord."

439
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:21,000
 So we come with fasting, and we seek God through prayer.

440
00:33:21,000 --> 00:33:24,000
 And then as we make the space, we pray,

441
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:27,000
 and we draw close to God through His Word,

442
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:30,000
 where we give God space to speak to us,

443
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:37,000
 to speak life over you and into your life.

444
00:33:37,000 --> 00:33:39,000
 And God loves doing that,

445
00:33:39,000 --> 00:33:44,000
 and He wants to do this shaping and forming, transforming work in us.

446
00:33:44,000 --> 00:33:48,000
 I want to invite the worship team to come up.

447
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:50,000
 And here's the thing.

448
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:55,000
 At the beginning, I talked about how we enter 2026

449
00:33:55,000 --> 00:34:01,000
 and that we might be holding quite different feelings.

450
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:04,000
 But I'm confident of this,

451
00:34:04,000 --> 00:34:09,000
 that if we walk through 2026 seeking God,

452
00:34:09,000 --> 00:34:13,000
 if we seek Him and make ourselves available to Him

453
00:34:13,000 --> 00:34:16,000
 to speak in our lives, to work in our lives,

454
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:21,000
 that this will be a year that is much better

455
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:24,000
 because you made space for God in your life.

456
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:28,000
 Because God, He loves you.

457
00:34:28,000 --> 00:34:34,000
 He's able and powerful to do immeasurably more than you can ask or imagine.

458
00:34:34,000 --> 00:34:37,000
 His grace is sufficient for you.

459
00:34:37,000 --> 00:34:40,000
 He can turn ashes into beauty,

460
00:34:40,000 --> 00:34:43,000
 mourning into dancing.

461
00:34:43,000 --> 00:34:47,000
 And so let's do this year with God.

462
00:34:47,000 --> 00:34:49,000
 I know I need Him.

463
00:34:49,000 --> 00:34:52,000
 2026, I can't do 2026 without God.

464
00:34:52,000 --> 00:34:56,000
 So I want to challenge you and invite you.

465
00:34:56,000 --> 00:35:00,000
 Let's fast together.

466
00:35:00,000 --> 00:35:04,000
 Let's come before Him

467
00:35:04,000 --> 00:35:07,000
 by carving out space and surrendering and saying,

468
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:12,000
 "Lord, I need you.

469
00:35:12,000 --> 00:35:16,000
 And I desire for you to powerfully work in our lives."

470
00:35:16,000 --> 00:35:18,000
 And I believe that when we do that,

471
00:35:18,000 --> 00:35:21,000
 that God will meet you.

472
00:35:21,000 --> 00:35:24,000
 And if we think of the end of 2026,

473
00:35:24,000 --> 00:35:30,000
 that there will be testimonies of how God has met us in our 2026

474
00:35:30,000 --> 00:35:33,000
 because we have been seeking, because we have been walking with Him,

475
00:35:33,000 --> 00:35:36,000
 because we have made room for Him to work in our lives.

476
00:35:36,000 --> 00:35:39,000
 Can I get an amen, church?

477
00:35:39,000 --> 00:35:40,000
 I want to invite you all to stand.

478
00:35:40,000 --> 00:35:44,000
 I would love to pray over us.

479
00:35:44,000 --> 00:35:52,000
 If you want to express, yeah, just your heart and your openness for God,

480
00:35:52,000 --> 00:35:54,000
 you can stretch out your hands before you.

481
00:35:54,000 --> 00:35:55,000
 It's just a sign of openness.

482
00:35:55,000 --> 00:35:58,000
 "Lord, I need you in my life in 2026."

483
00:35:58,000 --> 00:36:00,000
 You can just put your hands before.

484
00:36:00,000 --> 00:36:03,000
 So let me pray over us.

485
00:36:03,000 --> 00:36:08,000
 Heavenly Father, thank you that you are Lord over 2026,

486
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:15,000
 that you hold our lives, our community's lives, this world in your hands.

487
00:36:15,000 --> 00:36:17,000
 Thank you that you love us,

488
00:36:17,000 --> 00:36:21,000
 that you are committed to every single one of us here,

489
00:36:21,000 --> 00:36:24,000
 that you are faithful, that you cannot be unfaithful.

490
00:36:24,000 --> 00:36:25,000
 You are faithful.

491
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:28,000
 You're perfectly faithful.

492
00:36:28,000 --> 00:36:31,000
 Lord, and you know where everyone's at on this journey,

493
00:36:31,000 --> 00:36:34,000
 how they're stepping into this year.

494
00:36:34,000 --> 00:36:38,000
 Lord, and I pray that as we come, as we seek you through fasting,

495
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:42,000
 through prayer, through your word, that you will meet us,

496
00:36:42,000 --> 00:36:48,000
 that you will meet your people, that you will pour out your spirit,

497
00:36:48,000 --> 00:36:55,000
 that you give us by your spirit the strength and the grace that we need for 2026.

498
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:59,000
 And I pray that we will--Lord, I ask that we would get to know you

499
00:36:59,000 --> 00:37:01,000
 in a way that we have not known you before,

500
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:03,000
 that we will know you in a deeper way,

501
00:37:03,000 --> 00:37:07,000
 that we will have greater faith as we walk through 2026

502
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:10,000
 because of how you are meeting us this year.

503
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:13,000
 And so I just pray for a blessing.

504
00:37:13,000 --> 00:37:15,000
 I pray for provision.

505
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:18,000
 I pray for your mercy and your grace over our lives.

506
00:37:18,000 --> 00:37:24,000
 I pray for community, that you put us together with each other,

507
00:37:24,000 --> 00:37:27,000
 that we don't do this alone,

508
00:37:27,000 --> 00:37:33,000
 that you give us supernatural appointments of new connections

509
00:37:33,000 --> 00:37:36,000
 that we can journey with.

510
00:37:36,000 --> 00:37:41,000
 And so we lift all this up to you and say we love you, Jesus,

511
00:37:41,000 --> 00:37:43,000
 and we pray all this in your name.

512
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:45,000
 Amen.

